                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman</hi> 162 <hi rend="italic">T</hi>). I received this crown (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) from Mrs. Lewis.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18670506-name-66" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18670506-name-66" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670506-name-66" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18670506-name-66" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to her Majesty's Mint—this is a fragment of a bad half-crown—these two crowns are bad and from the same mould.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186705060010"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I know nothing about the charge of 30th March. I never was in Chelsea on Saturday night. I put down a florin to pay for a scarf, and the man said that it was a bad half-crown. I said that it could not be, for I had not a half-crown in my possession.</p>
